parameters: Don't let any other customers out, got it?

Section Chief: Can I really trust you with this!?
Yeah, relax. It's a referral from Akane, you know?

Section Chief: Then I'll trust you... but at least let me do this
much.
I am grateful.

I underestimated the job of waiting tables, but it's quite a
physically demanding job indeed.

(However, I still haven't come across the information I
desire. It's frustrating.)

(What to do... Should I continue to cast my net in this
establishment a bit longer? Or should I try a different

What's that noise near the entrance of the shop? It's a bit
loud.
Hey, Manager. What's going on?

Section Chief: Ah, it's you. Well, you see, there's a group of
rough types causing a ruckus in front of the shop, and it's
quite troubling.
Doesn't this place have its own security or bouncers?
Section Chief: Of course, we do.

Section Chief: But, you see, we thought they were just common
thugs, but they seem to have brought something strange with
them. They're letting it run wild and we can't handle it.
I see.

(Given the nature of this district, one can't expect much
from an orderly security force. No, these kinds of
establishments wouldn't rely on them in the first place...)
Hey, are you alright...!!

Everyone, it's dangerous here! Move away from this area!
Manager, I'm counting on you to take care of this man.

(I'd prefer not to stand out, but I can't ignore a situation
like this. If customers can't enter, it will hinder my
objectives. Either way, I can't just leave it be.)
Section Chief: I-I understand, but what about you?

You needn't worry about me. Leave this place to Knight
Reisha. Understood?

(It looks like a fight is inevitable. I should take this
opportunity to prepare for battle...)

(She's unconscious. It doesn't seem to be a fatal wound, but
the signs of beating are severe...)
Section Chief: B-Be safe and come back in one piece!!
